    <h1 class="title" style="font-size:34px;">About Citizen Knowledge</h1>
  </header>

  <main>
    <p style="font-size:18px;">I'm Greg Lewis, author of <em>The Performance of Obedience</em>, a book about the systems of law, authority, and bureaucracy we're all expected to navigate, and often expected to simply accept.</p>
    <p style="font-size:18px;">Citizen Knowledge is where that thinking meets the present. Each post takes a handful of stories from that day's news and looks at what they reveal about power, process, and the rules we live under, the kind of patterns the book explores in more depth, playing out in real time.</p>
    <p style="font-size:18px;">You don't need to have read the book to get something from this. Each post stands on its own. If you're someone who's ever felt talked down to by a system, a form, or an institution that assumed you wouldn't push back, this is written for you.</p>
    <p style="font-size:18px;">The Performance of Obedience is currently in submission to publishers. Updates on that will appear here when there's something worth reporting.</p>
    <p style="font-size:18px;">New posts most weekdays. Sign up below to get them as they land.</p>

    <div class="signup-block">
